# DedgeAuth i18n Support

## Required Files

- `wwwroot/i18n/nb.json` — Norwegian translations (default language)
- `wwwroot/i18n/en.json` — English translations
- Both files must have the **exact same set of keys**

## Required HTML

Add before closing `</body>`, after `user.js`:

```html
<script src="api/DedgeAuth/ui/i18n.js"></script>
```

## HTML Patterns

Static text elements:

```html
<h1 data-i18n="page.title">Page Title</h1>
<th data-i18n="table.email">Email</th>
<button data-i18n="button.save">Save</button>
```

Input placeholders:

```html
<input data-i18n-placeholder="placeholder.search" placeholder="Search...">
```

HTML content (entities, links):

```html
<a data-i18n-html="nav.back">&#8592; Back</a>
```

## JavaScript Pattern

For dynamically rendered text:

```javascript
const text = DedgeAuth.t('table.email', 'Email');
const msg = DedgeAuth.t('message.count', { count: 5 });
```

## Key Naming Convention

| Prefix | Usage | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| `nav.*` | Navigation items | `nav.dashboard`, `nav.settings` |
| `page.*` | Page titles | `page.title`, `page.subtitle` |
| `table.*` | Table headers | `table.email`, `table.name` |
| `button.*` | Button labels | `button.save`, `button.cancel` |
| `label.*` | Form labels | `label.email`, `label.password` |
| `placeholder.*` | Input placeholders | `placeholder.search` |
| `message.*` | User messages | `message.success`, `message.error` |
| `dialog.*` | Modal/dialog text | `dialog.confirm` |

## Rules

- Norwegian (`nb`) is the default language — all users start with Norwegian
- English text in HTML serves as fallback if translation is missing
- No `Program.cs` changes needed — `DedgeAuth.Client` auto-registers `/api/i18n/` endpoints via `MapDedgeAuthProxy()`
- Every visible text element in HTML must have a `data-i18n` attribute
- No hardcoded user-facing strings in JavaScript without `DedgeAuth.t()` wrapper
- Translation quality: use natural Norwegian Bokmål, not machine translation

